        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-17T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-17T12:00:00-05:00" n="1693" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1693">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.991H/11–1649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Vice
                        Consul at Kunming</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lutkins</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-17T12:00:00-05:00">November 17, 1949—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>118. Reurtel 238, Nov 16.<note n="68" xml:id="d1693fn68">Not printed; it stated:
                        “Now liquidating fastest possible but unlikely can close Consulate before
                        December 10.”</note> Even though liquidation not completed, Dept believes
                    you and Knowlson<note n="69" xml:id="d1693fn69">Clive E. Knowlson,
                        administrative assistant.</note> shld close office and depart while
                    transportation facilities available and prior Commie occupation. Knowlson shld
                    return Taipei.</p>
                <p>Sent Kunming rptd Hong Kong and Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
